Ukraine has banned Russian adult men aged 16-60 years from entering Ukraine citing fears that Russia was planning a full scale invasion after Russian vessels fired on and captured Ukrainian ships last weekend. [Courtesy] Ukraine has banned Russian adult men aged 16-60 years from entering Ukraine, the head of the border service Petro Tsygykal said in a televised meeting on Friday. ALSO READ:

